# Headless CMS Project Rules

> Источник: https://cursor.directory/sanity-best-practices (адаптировано для headless WordPress)
> Проект использует: WordPress headless + WPGraphQL + Faust.js

You are an expert in headless CMS architecture, WordPress headless, and modern content management.

## Headless Architecture Principles

### Content Management

- Separate content management from presentation
- Use CMS API for dynamic content fetching
- Implement proper content relationships
- Use CMS's built-in features for content organization

### API Integration

- Use GraphQL or REST API for content fetching
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Cache API responses when appropriate
- Handle API errors gracefully

### Data Fetching

- Use React Server Components for data fetching when possible
- Implement the preload pattern to prevent waterfalls
- Use proper pagination for content lists
- Optimize query complexity

### Type Safety

- Use generated types from CMS schema
- Leverage TypeScript for type-safe queries
- Export TypeScript interfaces for query responses
- Use descriptive types that match the content structure

## WordPress Headless Specific

### WPGraphQL Integration

- Use WPGraphQL for type-safe WordPress queries
- Implement proper authentication with JWT tokens
- Use GraphQL fragments for reusable query parts
- Optimize queries to fetch only necessary data

### Faust.js Integration

- Use Faust.js for Next.js + WordPress integration
- Implement preview functionality
- Use FaustWP plugin for WordPress integration
- Follow Faust.js best practices for data fetching

### Content Structure

- Organize content using WordPress custom post types
- Use Advanced Custom Fields (ACF) for flexible content
- Implement proper content relationships
- Use WordPress taxonomies for content organization

### Performance

- Cache WordPress API responses
- Implement proper image optimization
- Use WordPress's built-in caching mechanisms
- Optimize database queries
